Module kivakit.settings

Interface SettingsStore

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseResourceSettingsStore, BaseSettingsStore, Deployment, MemorySettingsStore, ResourceFolderSettingsStore, SettingsRegistry
public interface SettingsStore extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.registry.RegistryTrait, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, Iterable<Object>
Service Provider API

A store of SettingsObjects.

NOTE: This store object should not be accessed directly by user code. Instead, use SettingsTrait.

Loading and Saving

If the method supports(AccessMode) returns true for SettingsStore.AccessMode.LOAD, then settings can be loaded with load(). If the the store supports SettingsStore.AccessMode.SAVE, then save(SettingsObject) can be used to save a settings object.

Hash/Equals Contract

Note that it is not necessary for settings Objects to implement the Object.hashCode() / Object.equals(Object) contract. The SettingsObject.SettingsObjectIdentifier class implements this contract, allowing SettingsObjects to be accessed in maps and stored in sets.

jonathanl (shibo)
